(14, 'Sparkly', 'This week\'s theme: sparkly! Synth-y, shimmering, electronic goodness. I talk about dancing in the studio, deadlines stress, and how I envision Fetty Wap.', 'https://www.mixcloud.com/jackie-sun2/sundaze-week-2-oct-22-2017/', 39, '2017-10-24 21:53:59', '2017-11-08 18:39:52', '2017-10-22'),
(15, 'Arts Show #3', 'Tune in for chats about the merging of indigenous and Western myth in art; responses to a politically turbulent year in the Edinburgh Short Film Festival, and more! /////\r\n\r\n2.30: Interview with Scottish Storytelling Centres artist in residence Travis De Vries ////\r\n\r\n26.20: Interview with Paul Bruce, director of the Edinburgh Short Film Festival ////\r\n\r\n38.18: Interview with Tilly and Andra from A View from the Bridge at Bedlam Theatre ////\r\n\r\n48.45: Anna\'s Upcoming Artist of the Week, Kat! Find her on insta at @geometryforbeginners', 'https://www.mixcloud.com/FreshAirArts18/arts-show-3-25102017/', 7, '2017-10-28 19:18:55', '2017-10-28 19:32:21', '2017-10-25'),
(16, 'Arts Show #2', 'Groovy feminist art chat, an intersectional show about disabled drag queens, and lots more from the past week!\r\n\r\n02.50: Issey interviews Allolune aka Alice Carnegie, and reviews her exhibition \'Bubblegum\'\r\n\r\n19.50: Sian reviews \'Blanche and Butch\' at Summerhall\r\n\r\n31.50: Helen interviews David Ahmad from \'The Kite Runner\' at King\'s Theatre\r\n\r\n51.30: Kathrine interviews Eilidh and Becca from \'Number, Please.\' at Bedlam Theatre\r\n\r\n59.00: Kathrine and Ciara review \'Hedda Gabler\' at Festival Theatre', 'https://www.mixcloud.com/FreshAirArts18/arts-show-2-181017/', 7, '2017-10-28 19:22:55', '2017-10-28 19:22:55', '2017-10-18'),
(17, 'Arts Show #1', 'The first Arts Show of the semester was a packed one!\r\n\r\nFeaturing discussions about elitism in the art world, the \'Black Students of Edinburgh\' photo exhibition, and what\'s going on in the theatre world this week:\r\n\r\n\r\n00:00:36 - Interview with Gina Isaacs, star of Kings Theatre\'s \'A Streetcar Named Desire\'\r\n\r\n00:19:07 - Fiona\'s interview with Michelle, co-founder of \'Travesty\' Drag Night\r\n\r\n00:31: 20 - Interview with Wami Aluko, student photographer of \'Black Students of Edinburgh\' campaign\r\n\r\n00:43:11 - Flora and Anna interview Freddie Thomas, curator of \'BONKERS Contemporary\'\r\n\r\n01:04:19 - Julie\'s theatre review: \'Jury Play\' and \'Cockpit\'\r\n\r\n01:18:20 - Interview with Abi and Amelia from \'SULK\' at Bedlam Theatre\r\n\r\n01.30.53 - Camilla\'s interview with Phil O\'Shea who runs \'Peter Pancakes\'', 'https://www.mixcloud.com/FreshAirArts18/fresh-air-arts-1-121017/', 7, '2017-10-28 19:29:54', '2017-10-28 19:29:54', '2017-10-11'),
(18, 'The Lost Songs', 'Every week, I put together a playlist of songs to play on my show. These are the songs that didn\'t make it onto the show, whether because it didn\'t fit the theme, or I ran out of time. However, they get their proper airtime in this show! I talk about how much I love Sidney Bechet, seeing Slow Magic live (spoiler: it was trippy), and overuse the phrase \"it\'s not Austrian music, but it\'s music.\"', 'https://www.mixcloud.com/jackie-sun2/the-lost-songs-oct-28-2017/', 39, '2017-10-29 15:51:59', '2017-11-08 18:39:40', '2017-10-28'),
