(246, 'BackTrack', 'Backtracking our way through the biggest music scenes in history', 'Join us bright and early for a journey through disco, Detroit techno, 70s Brit punk, 90s girl bands, reggae dub, Berlin techno and more ', 'backtrack', '2018-10-07 18:37:06', '2018-10-17 20:25:00', 'cover_photo.jpg'),
(247, 'Tan & the Sun', '', 'Ever worry that the entire world is just rapidly falling apart and that there is no faith left in humanity? Tune in to counteract that darkness with some woman-made sunshine, as each week, we will talk about new pieces of positive news combined with music, arts, stories, and everything in between!', 'tan-the-sun', '2018-10-07 18:37:22', '2018-10-08 14:58:27', '92ADC13E-C876-4747-9F19-B6CEC0751F42.jpg'),
(248, 'The Guilty Capitalist', '', 'The Guilty Capitalist', 'the-guilty-capitalist', '2018-10-07 18:37:34', '2018-10-07 18:37:34', NULL),
(249, 'Girls \'n\' Boys', '', 'Girls \'n\' Boys', 'girls-n-boys', '2018-10-07 18:37:51', '2018-10-07 18:37:51', NULL),
(250, 'Candid Shots', 'Hiphop', 'With your host Lucia Rodriguez, we get into the juicy hiphop topics of the week, sometimes discuss edgy news which may be controversial with our guest of the week.', 'candid-shots', '2018-10-07 18:38:04', '2018-11-09 23:40:50', 'B6044C07-D701-4D7D-A7C1-9FD4826B955C.jpeg'),
(251, 'The Big Questions', '', 'Lizzie Lewis and Josh Christopher aka Groovemeisters aka Meister and the Groove aka Edinburgh\'s most pengerz rhythm section radio presenting duo, ask each other some big questions for an hour. These could be about anything, but you can guarantee TWO (2) THINGS: it will get deep and profound AND it will be interspersed with music selections from our vastly differing tastes. Might have guests or something, but tbh we don\'t really have any other pals. Maybe cos we refer to ourselves as Groovemeisters. So be it.', 'the-big-questions', '2018-10-07 18:38:16', '2018-10-25 22:23:13', 'big_qs__2_.jpg'),
(252, 'Textual Feelings ', '', 'Textual Feelings ', 'textual-feelings', '2018-10-07 18:38:29', '2018-10-07 18:38:29', NULL),
(253, 'Off the Beaten Track ', '', 'Off the Beaten Track ', 'off-the-beaten-track', '2018-10-07 18:38:41', '2018-10-07 18:38:41', NULL),
(254, 'The Wrestling Wreview ', 'Where we wreview wrestling!', 'TOO SWEET', 'the-wrestling-wreview', '2018-10-07 18:39:15', '2018-12-02 14:35:33', 'hell-in-a-cell-100115-wwe-ftr_k5y0u0j6bmh1zd631fmr7utn.jpg'),
(255, 'The Xavi + Jamie Show', '', 'The Xavi + Jamie Show', 'the-xavi-jamie-show', '2018-10-07 18:39:28', '2018-10-07 18:39:28', NULL),
(256, 'FreshAir Breakfast Show  ', 'with George Simonds', 'FreshAir Breakfast Show with George Simonds', 'freshair-breakfast-show-fc89aea9-dce4-481d-94bc-f8e656526c56', '2018-10-07 18:41:36', '2018-10-07 18:41:36', NULL),
(257, 'The Bigger Pitcher', 'Escape your everyday and travel away: that time the radio studio became an airplane. ', 'How often, my friends, have you come back from travelling your pockets full of stories and ridiculous encounters only to realise that your family does.not.want.to.hear.about.it.anymore? Has anyone ever gently prodded at you with the sarcastic \'Oh my god you went to [thisplace?]? I didn\'t know\'? Are there tons of places you still want to explore? Or have you spent all your student money on coffee and so you\'re too broke to? \r\n                                                                                                                                     \r\nPerfect, all of these contradicting and complex cases are also what embody me. And so, what better than discussing it over a nice handful of tunes once a week on FreshAir? \r\n\r\nThis is a show about places and faces, riddled by the ghost of the \'gap ya\' - we will be exploring the world from the comforting nest of this radio studio to speak about all the countries and sights that exist: the customs and practices, the prejudices and realities of visitors, and escape - for a moment, the curdled mess that is our University year. \r\n', 'the-bigger-pitcher', '2018-10-07 18:41:50', '2018-10-19 10:27:04', '14937395_10207563459265538_6424373232580883127_n.jpg'),
(258, 'Bmus\'d MA\'tes', '', 'Bmus\'d MA\'tes', 'bmus-d-ma-tes', '2018-10-07 18:42:10', '2019-02-27 12:24:52', '50992451_1589510021192530_856759925882224640_n.jpg'),
(259, 'Soul Therapy', '', 'Soundtracking your Friday lunchtime with the crme de la crme of soul, funk, disco and beyond, all accompanied by therapeutic life advice adapted practically from the greatest minds of all time. The smoothest and most jubilant way to get into your weekend.', 'soul-therapy', '2018-10-07 18:42:26', '2019-02-06 19:06:03', 'Cruzada.png'),
(260, '-', '', '!', '9ada34bf-92a8-4654-88e9-fe8e617cdcbe', '2018-10-07 18:42:37', '2019-02-18 09:08:28', NULL),
(261, 'FreshAir Music Hub Show', 'with Carly Beehler', 'FreshAir Music Hub Show with Carly Beehler', 'freshair-music-hub-show', '2018-10-07 18:43:14', '2018-10-07 18:43:57', NULL),
(262, 'The Fresh Lounge', '\"like the live lounge but local\"', 'Every Friday 5-6, tune in for some fresh mixes with DJ Bean (Fi Halliday) followed by a range of live performances and chit-chat with co-hosts Rachel and Sean O\'B.', 'the-fresh-lounge', '2018-10-07 18:43:25', '2019-03-17 18:29:36', 'freshlounge__2_.jpg'),
(263, ' Nostalgia, Ultra ', '', 'Particular albums and songs hold a significant resonance during certain times in our lives. They permanently mark our hearts, acting as the soundtrack to specific memories and experiences. Each week we will explore a different theme, chat to a young person from the Edinburgh community about an album that is special to them, and discuss how that album reflects and helps to further examine the weeks theme.', 'nostalgia-ultra', '2018-10-07 18:43:36', '2018-11-14 22:32:53', 'Nostalgia__Ultra_logo.jpg'),
(264, 'FreshAir Sports Hub Show', 'with Dan Brookes', 'FreshAir Sports Hub Show with Dan Brookes', 'freshair-sports-hub-show', '2018-10-07 18:44:32', '2018-10-07 18:44:32', NULL),
(265, 'The HomeVybz Show', '', 'The HomeVybz Show', 'the-homevybz-show', '2018-10-07 18:44:43', '2018-10-07 18:44:43', NULL),
(266, 'L\'Heure de la Bande de la Zac Brun Bande Heure', '', 'L\'Heure de la Bande de la Zac Brun Bande Heure', 'l-heure-de-la-bande-de-la-zac-brun-bande-heure', '2018-10-07 18:44:54', '2018-10-07 18:44:54', NULL),
(267, 'Just Saying', '', 'Weekly dose of pops hottest new releases and a serving of throwbacks from the pop archives! What better way to start your Saturday?', 'just-saying', '2018-10-07 18:45:07', '2018-10-20 22:12:45', 'B68C9BC4-5BC0-4208-A7EC-B0CC72B65415.jpeg'),
(268, 'The North South Divide', '', 'Two students reconciling their geographical differences through good tunes and good chat!', 'the-north-south-divide', '2018-10-07 18:45:17', '2019-02-03 11:30:10', 'ns_divide_logo.png'),
(269, 'Escape to the Country', '', 'Escape to the Country', 'escape-to-the-country', '2018-10-07 18:45:31', '2018-10-07 18:45:31', NULL),
(270, 'It\'s All Happening', '', 'Every week I do a deep dive into a certain genre, a certain decade, sometimes a certain place, and give you all the music you need to know from the hits to the ones that passed you by', 'it-s-all-happening', '2018-10-07 18:45:42', '2018-10-21 14:00:23', 'fullsizeoutput_1555.jpeg'),
(271, 'EMPTY HEAD', '', 'Tune into EMPTY HEAD at 13:00 every Thursday to discover which year will be put under the musical microscope! No year is without its moments but what exactly does twelve months sound like? Each week we will be selecting a year at random and going on to talk about the pop-culture and political phenomenons through the music that was released, the music that was charting and the songs that weren\'t. We\'ll be doing it all! From the beginnings of Disco coinciding with the end of Nixon in 1974, Thatcher\'s Privatization and the explosion of Synth Pop in 1981, the second wave of Soviet Jazz under Khrushchev\'s Thaw in 1953 and the music of Tokyo Rose\'s propaganda show in the Pacific War on \'45. ENJOY!!!!', 'empty-head', '2018-10-07 18:45:51', '2019-02-01 18:32:25', 'Screen_Shot_2019-02-01_at_18.31.56.png'),
(272, 'Well into the Eighties', '', 'Well into the Eighties', 'well-into-the-eighties', '2018-10-07 18:46:01', '2018-10-20 17:42:41', 'wellinto2.jpg'),
(273, 'Cover Story', '', 'Cover Story', 'cover-story', '2018-10-07 18:46:14', '2018-10-07 18:46:14', NULL),
(274, 'Stories', '', 'A celebration of storytelling in our lives; Stories\' with Brnagh Grace is a weekly hour of telling and discussing stories  tales thatll make you laugh, cry, reflect, learn or simply smile. My Story sees me share a personal story derived from the past seven days of my life whilst Fresh Ink provides a platform for the reading and discussion of new, creative and life writing. Around the kitchen table ensures a cosy setting for laid-back story-sharing chats with family and friends, meanwhile, I also take a look at stories from the arts; highlighting films, theatre, literature and music and the tales they try to tell. Not to mention theres a fairytale soundtrack to complement our stories, including the Songs for Bookworms literary musical treat! \r\n\r\nSend in your stories, personal or creative. Prose, poetry, drama, music, anything youve created, Id love to feature you on the show! \r\n\r\nFacebook: Stories with Brnagh Grace.\r\nEmail: storieswithbronagh@gmail.com\r\n\r\n', 'stories', '2018-10-07 18:46:40', '2018-11-15 01:02:40', 'IMG_E2912.jpg'),
(275, 'PRACTISING for PARTIES', 'by NAJA MAHLER and CHRISTOPHER LIGHTFOOT', 'NAJA MAHLER and CHRISTOPHER LIGHTFOOT aren\'t good at parties. So this is where they practice.\r\n\r\nExpect two friends talking about their weeks, maybe some things interested have them in the news, and the songs they\'ve been listening to. By doing this, NAJA and CHRIS hope they will have the materials they need as the go forward into the world.\r\n\r\nPRACTISING for PARTIES is about fun times and good music. With NAJA due to soon move away, the on-air party reminds us of the parties we\'ve been to, the stories we\'ve shared--but most important, the glimmering, fragile moments of friendship.\r\n\r\nWe air every Saturday night between 9PM and 10PM. Guests vary. Join in.', 'practising-for-parties', '2018-10-07 18:46:59', '2018-11-03 19:58:53', '43629470_296903374475436_3539244375517167616_n.jpg'),
(276, 'MoJo', '', 'The show that takes a particular moment in music history and explores all that it has to offer; great music, interviews and everything in between.\r\n\r\nFacebook - @MoJoEdinburgh\r\nEmail - mojoedinburgh@gmail.com', 'mojo', '2018-10-07 21:09:18', '2018-10-08 20:41:31', 'IMG_0493.jpg'),
(277, 'Banana Pancakes', 'Music, food, really bad jokes, and whatever Kanye has been up to this time', 'Just guys being dudes, on a Sunday morning.', 'banana-pancakes', '2018-10-08 19:10:55', '2019-02-28 17:55:06', 'banana_pancakes.jpg'),
(278, 'EDI-Live!', 'Presenter - Benji Sumrie', 'Hello!\r\n\r\nI\'m Benji Sumrie and I host an Arts show which I hope you will all enjoy! My show is everything to do with the arts; that means music, film, theatre and much much more! Topics vary from week to week filled with interesting facts, case studies, events happening in Edinburgh and topped off with some of my favourite tracks inbetween!\r\n\r\nI do love talking about the Arts in general and I hope you do too. Many thanks to everyone in the FreshAir.org.uk team for giving me this wonderful oppotunity, it\'s a blast! I am always welcome to suggestions so give me a buzz if you want!\r\n\r\nGive me a listen and, sit back, relax and enjoy ', 'edi-live', '2018-10-08 19:13:10', '2018-10-28 14:15:59', 'IMG_20171102_190443_524.jpg'),
(279, 'Comprehensively Bowled', 'Weekly dose of the Cricketing action with a healthy blend of British music.', 'Cricket show with a backdrop of British music. Bringing you the latest news and opinion on the world of cricket as well as features to expand your cricketing knowledge.', 'comprehensively-bowled', '2018-10-08 19:14:53', '2018-11-11 22:00:30', 'Logo_Final.jpg'),
(280, 'The Pop Playlist', 'The best new pop, indie-pop and indie-rock...', 'Join Felix every Wednesday from 10-11am for an hour of the best new pop music! We\'ll also play classics that you know and love, as well as some tracks that you will be sure to love in the future! Get involved on Twitter: @EdiPopPlaylist', 'the-pop-playlist', '2018-10-08 19:15:18', '2019-03-19 20:59:53', 'thumbnail_IMG_3631.jpg'),
(281, 'Rhythmic Rotations', '', 'Rhythmic Rotations', 'rhythmic-rotations', '2018-10-09 22:10:22', '2018-10-09 22:10:22', NULL),
(283, 'Squarewaves', '', 'A music and talk show, with guest features.', 'squarewaves', '2019-02-01 14:18:59', '2019-02-03 03:49:54', NULL),
(285, 'FreshAir Breakfast Show      ', 'with James Ellis', 'FreshAir Breakfast Show with James Ellis', 'freshair-breakfast-show-a292d8d5-40ea-4bc8-85d4-b2c6e9284530', '2019-02-02 20:12:05', '2019-02-02 20:12:05', NULL),
(286, 'Benji Sumrie\'s Breakfast Show                     ', 'with Benji Sumrie', 'This is my early morning breakfast show where I talk about new topics within our socially dynamic world, all being intertwined within the Arts. This is to do with arts, film, media and the entertainment industry. Hope you enjoy!', 'benji-sumrie-s-breakfast-show', '2019-02-02 20:13:48', '2019-02-07 14:18:58', 'actor_with__resized.jpg'),
(287, 'FreshAir Breakfast Show     ', 'with Jack Titley', 'Jack Titley gets you into your Thursday groove every week, with interviews, storytelling, discussion, outstanding tunes and more! Follow us on Twitter @FreshAirThurs', 'freshair-breakfast-show-bd183592-bfce-4622-b565-fb36cc9b9635', '2019-02-02 20:14:58', '2019-02-06 19:39:09', 'Cruzada__1_.png'),
(288, 'FreshAir Breakfast Show       ', 'with Sophie Smith and Xavi Bird', 'FreshAir Breakfast Show with Sophie Smith and Xavi Bird', 'freshair-breakfast-show-36842451-7460-4df9-a90e-48f76b50ba6e', '2019-02-02 20:16:17', '2019-02-02 20:16:17', NULL),
(289, 'Inverted Commas', '', '<3', 'inverted-commas', '2019-02-03 03:38:12', '2019-02-18 09:09:09', 'IMG_5149.JPG'),
(290, 'Give Me Space', '', 'Calm space-themed show about NASA and SpaceX as well as interesting futuristic new technology and scifi featuring varied guests and a mix of spaced out music ( mostly hip hop and indie rock).', 'give-me-space', '2019-02-03 03:38:53', '2019-02-03 03:38:53', NULL),
(291, 'Two Swift Halves', '', 'We plan to have a show involving music and chat, playing both well known tunes and personal favourites listeners may not have heard. We will then include entertaining segments each week, one of which is described on our demo.', 'two-swift-halves', '2019-02-03 03:41:48', '2019-02-03 03:41:48', NULL),
(292, 'The X Effect', '', 'The X Effect is a weekly talk show on the effects of xenophobia on immigrant-identifying peoples within the UK. The show invites guest speakers on every week who self-identify as immigrants within the UK to talk about migration and intersection issues such as gender, class and race. It intends to provide a platform where immigrants can talk openly about their lived experience while celebrating the UK\'s diverse immigrant artists, writers, and musicians. ', 'the-x-effect', '2019-02-03 03:44:06', '2019-02-03 03:44:06', NULL),
(293, 'Agony Ishbel and Friends', 'Oh so you think you\'re the only person who has friends?', 'Agony Ishbel and Useless Producer James love to help people, and help they will on Agony Ishbel and Friends. Agony Ishbel will be solving problems for their fantastic listeners live in the studio and she might even give up the reigns to special guest broadcasters if what they want is to host a radio show for an hour. It\'ll be a multi-dimensional trip through the radio cosmos with Agony Ishbel, Useless Producer James and Friends.', 'agony-ishbel-and-friends', '2019-02-03 03:45:20', '2019-02-17 19:00:57', 'Agony_Ishbel_and_Friends_Promo.jpg'),
(294, 'Some of you didn\'t listen to 8tracks and it really shows', '', 'Music based show reminiscing about the site 8tracks and playing some of its most iconic songs and new music that former listeners of 8tracks would love. If when you were fourteen you pretended to you liked the film Pulp Fiction then this show would be for you. A safe space for the open admissions of pretentious indie youth culture which we have hopefully grown out of- anyway with that said here\'s Wonderwall. ', 'some-of-you-didn-t-listen-to-8tracks-and-it-really-shows', '2019-02-03 03:45:37', '2019-02-06 00:37:35', 'IMG_7083.JPG'),
(295, 'The \'How to\' Guide', '', 'The themed music-chat show giving you useless advice on how to live life! We\'ll chat about the topic of the week, play some songs and have a good chat on air... and listen out for the weekly quiz too! ', 'the-how-to-guide', '2019-02-03 03:45:57', '2019-03-13 22:13:56', NULL),
(296, 'Processing Processes', '', 'Breaking down the mundane and the routine into something more.', 'processing-processes', '2019-02-03 03:46:15', '2019-02-03 03:46:15', NULL),
(297, 'Afternoon Tea', '', 'We are a pop culture chat show. Each episode we will dissect that week\'s celebrity gossip (and other news), with songs inbetween! ', 'afternoon-tea', '2019-02-03 03:47:08', '2019-02-03 03:47:08', NULL),
(298, 'The Complainers', '', 'We take the weeks disasters and complain live on air with some tunes! Guests may feature for an actual \'valid complaint\', whereas we (the hosts) will be lighthearted. People can phone in too!', 'the-complainers', '2019-02-03 03:48:36', '2019-02-03 03:48:36', NULL),
(299, 'Em Nicks and Guests', '', 'Each week I will be talking to different people about how they fill their time and what they are interested in outside of uni life - giving you the chance to learn more about particular topics. There will also be frequent discussion about mental health and ways to help cope with the stresses and strains of uni life. Lots of music played throughout.\r\n\r\n', 'em-nicks-and-guests', '2019-02-03 03:49:25', '2019-02-07 10:17:48', NULL),
(300, 'Let\'s Rewind', '', 'This will be a music show where I pick a year from 1965 - 2018 at random and play a selection of music from that specific year. I am a music fanatic and have compiled my favorite albums from every year so this would be a good opportunity to show listeners the various sounds and themes that dominated music from a particular year and can display music history in an interesting way. Multiple genres will be played, guests would be very rare if ever, and no special equipment would be required.', 'let-s-rewind', '2019-02-03 03:50:11', '2019-02-03 03:50:11', NULL),
(301, 'Four Weddings and a Tuna Roll', '', 'Two freshers discussing day to day problems that friends and themselves have encountered with a mix of classic tuna in between.', 'four-weddings-and-a-tuna-roll', '2019-02-03 03:50:44', '2019-02-04 12:35:07', 'image.jpg'),
(302, 'Tracks for Trains', '', 'Long, winding tunes and long-winded conversation.', 'tracks-for-trains', '2019-02-03 03:51:20', '2019-02-04 22:49:02', 'logofinal.jpg'),
(303, 'It\'s A London Thing', '', 'A music show celebrating uk music, across a variety of different genres.', 'it-s-a-london-thing', '2019-02-03 03:52:03', '2019-02-03 03:52:03', NULL),
(304, 'A Slice of Cherry Pie and a Cup of Coffee', '', 'The show is based around the theme of happiness and positivity where I share all the things that have been making me happy that week, from films, TV shows, and good songs to fun news stories and personal anecdotes. I\'ll be both playing lots of music, and having a good chat! Tune in Wednesdays 4-5pm.', 'a-slice-of-cherry-pie-and-a-cup-of-coffee', '2019-02-03 03:52:45', '2019-02-03 15:39:49', 'a_slice_of_cherry_pie.jpg'),
(305, 'Crepuscular Rays', '', 'Crepuscular Rays is an ambient music show tailored for study and relaxation. ', 'crepuscular-rays', '2019-02-03 03:53:12', '2019-02-05 13:37:55', 'Screen_Shot_2019-02-04_at_18.43.28.png'),
(306, 'Mind Yourself', '', 'A chat show based on issues surrounding mental health and self care, with occasional features from guests and feel good tunes. To share your story/ apply to be a guest contact us on mindyourself.freshair@gmail.com', 'mind-yourself', '2019-02-03 03:53:50', '2019-02-16 14:47:13', 'Mind_Yourself.jpg'),
(307, 'Our Child', '', 'A comedic talk show featuring alternative and heavy music.', 'our-child', '2019-02-03 03:55:11', '2019-02-03 03:55:11', NULL),
(308, 'Lacasa Culture', '', 'It is a music hiphop show where we play and discuss the new hiphop albums of the month. In the past we\'ve reviewed Jon Bellion, brang on guests to discuss the history of Wu-tang Clan, Tribe Called Quest and Outkast.', 'lacasa-culture', '2019-02-03 03:56:05', '2019-02-03 03:56:05', NULL),
(309, 'just some tunes', '', 'Music show, discovering new music and rediscovering old favourites. Will explore a range of different genres, from techno and house to classic rock. Includes segments such as music trivia, artist spotlights, and possibly interviews with local musicians and producers. ', 'just-some-tunes', '2019-02-03 03:56:27', '2019-02-03 03:56:27', NULL),
(310, 'palms, pineapples + peaches', '', 'palms, pineapples + peaches', 'palms-pineapples-peaches', '2019-02-03 03:56:58', '2019-02-03 03:56:58', NULL),
(311, 'Harvest', '', 'Harvest', 'harvest', '2019-02-03 03:57:44', '2019-02-03 03:57:44', NULL),
(312, 'Way Too Deep w/ DJ Langtal', '', 'Music show with a genre chosen as a theme for each week. Not a talk-show in general but will involve some chat with visiting DJs or musicians. Each week one interesting movie will be suggested and as well as events of interest in the region (with respect to the week\'s theme genre)', 'way-too-deep-w-dj-langtal', '2019-02-03 03:58:25', '2019-02-03 03:58:25', NULL),
(313, 'Hot Fudge Sundae', '', 'A chomp of swashbuckling trackadelica from around the world, loving music for music lovers and blending smokey soul-stacks from all walks of life. ', 'hot-fudge-sundae', '2019-02-03 03:59:14', '2019-02-03 03:59:14', NULL),
(314, 'Ladies who Lunch', '', 'Ladies Who Lunch is a show about recent popular culture and current affairs and gender and sex issues, discussed with a variety of different guests each week. There is so much happening in the current political climate and one of the benefits of being at such a diverse university is the diversity of opinions which we aim to reflect in the diversity of guests each week.', 'ladies-who-lunch', '2019-02-03 03:59:43', '2019-02-03 11:53:41', 'ladies_who_lunch_2.jpeg'),
(315, 'Aux Anixety', '', 'Aux Anxiety is a music show providing shareable songs for any occasion. We plan to have diverse weekly themes, ranging from study sessions to classic pres essentials. We plan to share our favorites, with a special focus on women and BME artists. We want to create a comfortable and exciting space for people to discover songs they might not have found on their own, and to get over their aux anxiety! ', 'aux-anixety', '2019-02-03 04:00:10', '2019-02-22 19:46:26', '16ad722463b1bb3ed3734e51bcde7acc.jpg'),
(316, 'Orange Juice', '', 'A comedy show with great music as well. It will be made up of different segments such as \"meadows share moments\" or \"liar in the booth\" as well as just general funny conversation. We may have guests as the show goes on. ', 'orange-juice', '2019-02-03 04:00:44', '2019-02-03 04:00:44', NULL),
(317, 'Immortal Vice', '', 'Primarily music focused and genre fluid, blending both dance and non-dance in a way that makes it all dance-able. Mostly electronic but can go in any direction.', 'immortal-vice', '2019-02-03 04:01:09', '2019-02-03 04:01:09', NULL),
(318, 'Amateur Hour', '', 'It is a talk show where people can send in their problems and gripes for Toby and I to discuss and potentially solve.', 'amateur-hour', '2019-02-03 04:01:53', '2019-02-03 04:01:53', NULL),
(319, 'Art Matters', '', 'Underground and up and coming music from cities across the world. I play a mix of indie-rock, shoegaze, experimental, minimalist, some psychedelic electronic, and pretty much anything that I absolutely love. ', 'art-matters', '2019-02-03 04:02:21', '2019-02-03 04:02:21', NULL),
(320, 'Endless Summer', '', 'Playing tunes ranging from reggae and soca to dancehall and afrobeats ~ bringing those carnival vibes aaaaall year round', 'endless-summer', '2019-02-03 04:02:42', '2019-03-05 20:14:38', '22179993_1618136048208009_7537702852670240554_o.jpg'),
(321, 'Hip Hop Hour', '', 'Hip hop music, with discussion of the world of hip hop in general ', 'hip-hop-hour', '2019-02-03 04:02:58', '2019-02-03 04:02:58', NULL),
(322, 'Wadiyatalkinabeat', '', 'Our show is gunna be based on trivia and interesting stories with a focus on providing relatable topics and current tunes for the listener.', 'wadiyatalkinabeat', '2019-02-03 04:03:21', '2019-02-03 04:03:21', NULL),
(323, 'mmoonmmusic', 'songs 4 the starz', 'dance music based around what the stars are saying, run by rowan ', 'mmoonmmusic', '2019-02-03 04:03:37', '2019-02-05 23:05:13', 'Screen_Shot_2019-01-31_at_20.44.34.png'),
